    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That \"shield\" analogy is interesting. If the weave is tight enough to block out things like dirt or moisture at a microscopic level, would it actually prevent small airborne particles or even tiny organisms from getting through the fibers? I'm trying to understand if this density level offers any kind of physical barrier to microscopic intrusion.",
